<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05036a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036a"> 36(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> I seek the Blessed One</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">One day a sick man came to Marmoutier, to ask St. Martin to cure him. The fist person he chanced to meet was Brice. &lsquo;<mark>I want the Blessed One</mark>,&rsquo; said the sick man, &lsquo;but I know neither where he is nor how he is occupied.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 75</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02035e" href="c02all.htm#c02035e">VI.C.02:035(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
